    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Detailed diagnostic assessment of Armenian police educational system is carried out, and its new model is defined (e.g. police educational models are revised, curricula audited).
2. New police training curriculum developed, learning modules tested.
3. ToT for Police Educational Center&#x2019;s lecturers is conducted.
4. Big data analytical tool for the Operational Management System is developed and tested.
5. Community policing model is reviewed and enhanced; corresponding SOPs are developed on the basis of good international practice.
6. Police Code of Ethics and Code of Conduct updated/developed.
7. Police communication strategy and action plan are revisited and adjusted to the needs.
8. Police digital transformation roadmap is developed, and digitalization piloting is implemented.
9. Institute of gender equality focal point in the Police is established.
10. Public awareness campaign to foster and ensure female roles within MoI and Police is conducted.
11. Crisis preparedness assessment and gap analysis and recommendations elaborated.
12. SOP for Crisis Management and Continuity of Police Business defined and implemented.
13. Interagency planning and coordination training workshops and regular drills executed.</narrative>
    </description>
